      "writtenOn": "2017-04-20T21:52:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Inline doesn\u0027t technically mean anything except, hey linker if you see two copies of this, don\u0027t worry I promise either\u0027s fine.\n\nSo, yes.  If you expect this to be called across a .dll boundary, yes.  If you don\u0027t, you probably want a static inline function.",
